pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

import "@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol";
import "@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721URIStorage.sol";
import "@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/Counters.sol";

contract FarmingCropNFT is ERC721URIStorage {
    using Counters for Counters.Counter;
    Counters.Counter private _tokenIds;

    constructor() ERC721("FarmingCrop", "FC") {}

    function createCropNFT(address to, string memory tokenURI) public returns (uint256) {
        _tokenIds.increment();
        uint256 newItemId = _tokenIds.current();
        _mint(to, newItemId);
        _setTokenURI(newItemId, tokenURI);
        return newItemId;
    }

    function destroyNFT(uint256 tokenId) public {
        require(msg.sender == ownerOf(tokenId), "You do not own this NFT");
        _burn(tokenId);
    }
}

This Solidity code provides you with the FarmingCropNFT contract which is based on the ERC721 standard provided by the OpenZeppelin contracts library. The main functions included are:

1. createCropNFT(): This function allows to create a new Crop NFT with a specific tokenURI which can contain other metadata for the crop.
2. destroyNFT(): This function is for NFT destruction. Only the owner of the NFT (which can be a farmer) can destroy it.

In the above code, the functionality for secondary trading and price fluctuation based on various factors is not developed. You can extend the contract or create a separate market contract to include this logic. The market contract will interact with the FarmingCropNFT contract to manage trades between parties. You can also choose to include other desired functionalities depending on your application requirements.

